                  <interp inst="t18231022-147-crimeloc791" type="placeName" value="New Court, Duck-lane, Westminster"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18231022-147-crimeloc791" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231022-147-off789 t18231022-147-crimeloc791"></join>. The prisoner went home with me on the 21st of October, at night, and stopped all night with me. He gave me one shilling, which he saw me put into my purse, which I put into my trunk; he gave me another shilling and stopped until half-past four o'clock in the morning; I then went to get a young woman to sleep with me for the rest of the night, and as I returned I met him going out; he shook hands with me. I laid till half-past seven; then missed my pocket-book, money, and duplicates.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18231022-147-person1265">
                  THOMAS 
                  PACE
               <interp inst="t18231022-147-person1265" type="surname" value="PACE"></interp>
