                     <interp inst="t18231022-147-person1265" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I apprehended the prisoner on Tuesday night, and found the purse in his fob. After he was committed his wife informed me I could find the pocket-book in Vine-street, which I did.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in liquor, and she persuaded me to go home with her; she let me out at five o'clock.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 32.</p>
